"Vodka has this advantage that they can mix it with fruit juice and so don't feel it," explains the head of the department.
Eva Jurinova, spokesman for the Motol Hospital, also gives her reason.
"In general, it's rum or fernet."
"Today is fashionable alcohol, especially in elementary schools."
"In some cases, it was slivovice that they brought back from the house," added Jurinova.
According to the Head of Department Pelikan, it is normal to see drunk children aged 13 to 14 in hospital.
Before working in Horovice since last year, he was in Motol where he practiced ten years in pediatrics where ambulances brought students from the wide surroundings completely drunk.
"A girl was hospitalized four times
