"She was at Holesovice Exhibition Park at a party."
"What's interesting is that it doesn't seem weird to the mother that her daughter is away for 48 hours," said the Director of the Department.
It is precisely the disinterest of parents or their unusual tolerance for their rejection of drinking that is the main cause of children's alcoholism.
According to experts, however, there is no mention of dependence, in its strict sense, on children.
"Under the term "alcoholic" we hear a chronic addiction to alcohol for several years with all the phenomena that result from it but that we do not find in children".
"In the case of those who use repeated alcohol, it is rather a significantly unfavourable socio-family background," explained the head of the Pelikan Department.
According to Jurinova, about forty drunk children were hospitalized this year until mid-November in the pediatric clinic in Motol.
Only cases with severe intoxication requiring hospitalization are integrated into the statistics.
Drunk children who are after emergency care taken home by parents or the police are not counted.
In addition to the cases of children who sit and drink a bottle of alcohol after school, according to Pelikan, there are three seasonal waves with which one can count: the day of witches, the Saint Sylvestre and the end of the school year.
"Or they drink in spite of bad results or on the contrary they celebrate the beginning of the holiday".
"Of course I experienced on witch day an admission of 7 drunk children at once," said Pelikan.
The drunken child who spent the night at the hospital in detoxification under medical supervision is paradoxically in a better position than the one who returned home and suffered the day after the "woody mouth".
Morning headaches caused by dehydration and glucose deficiency are eliminated by an infusion of glucose and nutrients that the body needs.
"That's why they're better off because they spend an excellent evening and then a gentle awakening and nothing hurts them."
"They are only surprised where they are," Pelikan adds, knowing that from time to time it spoils the good mood of patients at least with the note to pay for their care.
Ambulance transport and hospitalization on an intensive care bed can go up to tens of thousands of crowns.
"From time to time, I applied this as a means of education by counting to these children how much their drunkenness cost and that they could spend the whole summer in seasonal work to repay one evening," Pelikan added.
However, according to him, health insurance companies in their declining management, which should recover from parents the burden of care, do not deal with cases of drunken children.
