In addition, chopped steak, canned tuna, and even bread baguette and gum were stuffed with pesticides and other chemicals.
Nitrate and chloroform were found in tap water.
For dinner, salmon steak was the most "rich" with 34 chemical residues detected and even examination of the plastic plate used to heat the meal in the microwave was not exempt.
The final risk to the consumer of this "contaminant cocktail" is probably underestimated, according to the study.
The Alliance Europe Ecologie-Les Verts (EE-LV), for its part, proposed "in the face of the urgency of the situation" to establish a moratorium on the use of pesticides, in order to stop "the increase in diseases of civilization".
In July, a study by the European Food Safety Agency (EFSA) reported the presence of residues of 365 different pesticides identified in fruit and vegetables consumed in Europe, including 76 in cereals.
